When what you need is a quick chocolate fix, this cake will hit the spot. All you need is 3 tablespoons (44.4 ml) cocoa powder, 4 tablespoons sugar, 4 tablespoons flour, 3 tablespoons milk, and an egg. For a fudgy, gooey, extra-chocolatey version of this cake, skip the milk and add just one tablespoon of flour, or leave it out entirely. It will come out with a richer consistency. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/03\/Make-a-Cake-in-10-Minutes-Step-1Bullet1.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Cake-in-10-Minutes-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/03\/Make-a-Cake-in-10-Minutes-Step-1Bullet1.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Cake-in-10-Minutes-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

If you love the flavor of Nutella, add 3 tablespoons (44.4 ml) to the mix. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/09\/Make-a-Cake-in-10-Minutes-Step-1Bullet2.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Cake-in-10-Minutes-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/09\/Make-a-Cake-in-10-Minutes-Step-1Bullet2.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Cake-in-10-Minutes-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

You could also add a tablespoon or two of peanut butter if you're so inclined. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/f\/f7\/Make-a-Cake-in-10-Minutes-Step-1Bullet3.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Cake-in-10-Minutes-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/f\/f7\/Make-a-Cake-in-10-Minutes-Step-1Bullet3.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Cake-in-10-Minutes-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Espresso or brewed coffee add depth of flavor - throw in a teaspoon or two. Add a few shakes of cinnamon and cayenne pepper for a spicy variation.
